I like the fact that it's not a race against time. You're not penalized for making mistakes. Nobody cares how many moves you make, as long as you advance towards the solution. There's no points to collect either. 
This is a game that challenges your problem solving skills in a very relaxing way. 
However, that design choice creates a problem: the game does get harder as you advance to a higher level. The difficulty is mainly determined by the number of colors and tubes presented. 
The game can display a maximum of 12 tubes and 9 colors. There's only so many permutations the game can conjure up. So the difficulty level maxes out at about level 75.  It gets boring after that as it seems all the same.

I would rate it 4.5 stars if I could. I thinks it‚Äôs a really chill and relaxing game that has a nice mental challenge to it. I have two things that made me knock off a star from my rating. #1) I do wish there were less ads or at least an option to buy an ad-free version, because I know that I definitely would if it was available. Additionally, I often find myself closing and putting down the game every time an ad pops up because I get frustrated; if there were less ads, I would probably play the game more. #2) I appreciate that you can take you time playing this and there‚Äôs no timer, but because it‚Äôs a mental puzzle, I would enjoy seeing some sort of score letting you know how well you solved it. For example, did you solve it in the least number of moves? Or maybe just a clock showing you how quickly you solved it (you would have as long as long as you needed and there would be no time limit, but you could use it to gauge your progress)?

So I really do love the gameplay and the overall set up of the app. It‚Äôs very relaxing and has a nice aesthetic and vibe, I love playing. I am, however, very peeved about the ads. 
This wouldn‚Äôt be such a big issue if it was behind a paywall or something but I don‚Äôt even get that option, so rather than forking over $1.99 and never having to see ads again I‚Äôm constantly bombarded by ads every time I want to play and it‚Äôs gotten to the point where playing isn‚Äôt fun anymore cause I know I‚Äôll have to deal with unnecessary ads. I don‚Äôt understand why there‚Äôs not an option to just pay a fee to not see ads anymore, I‚Äôm perfectly fine with that as I have paid that fee beforehand with many other games I‚Äôve downloaded cause really at the end of the day the ads take so much out of the experience and is a huge downer. I‚Äôve been putting my phone in airplane mode to bypass the ads but then I‚Äôve got the issue where I can‚Äôt receive notifications or listen to music while I‚Äôm playing the game the way it should be played. 

Please for the love of god tone down the ads and put a permanent ad ban option in the app, I know there are people who aren‚Äôt willing to pay and might leave a bad review because of it but it‚Äôs so much better to have the option there to remove them then to just lock people into having to see ads so frequently.

I'd been playing this game for over a year, I'm at nearly 700 hundred levels. It was extremely fun and something I would play very often. Extremely satisfying and had you thinking more than a lot of other mobile games. 
 But the update to the game a few months ago completely ruined it for me. They changed the hub in this update, added different tubes and such. That's not the issue.
The issue is the suggestion. Whenever you wait for "too long" a white hand will pop up and point to what it thinks you should do next, like the undo or the add a new tube. This feature is infuriating to me.
 I've been playing for around a year and am at 650 levels, I know how to play. I don't need this hand popping up and pointing things out for me whenever I take too long to think. It's distracting and annoying. 
 It isn't even correct half the time, there's been times where it will suggest undoing and when I ignore it and keep going I'll complete the level regardless. I'm just very annoyed, as someone who has been playing for a while and very much enjoyed this game, that it's treating me like a new player.
I've stopped playing since it happened. Still have the app and hope it goes away at some point but I haven't played it in a long time. All im asking for is an off-or-on button for this feature and I'll keep playing the game. I have no other complaints besides this feature.

review_title: Do the math, watching ads for one hour a day is TOO much
review_description:
The game is fine, sort of. 
But if I play say, 30 levels in one day, even as I successfully complete one level I am FORCED to watch an ad. Boring repetitive ads for more games, and by the way, the ads are flash enhanced for games that do not contain the images in the ads. The ads are exploitative, showing poor homeless children that you have to tap to provide a jacket for, and again, you cannot avoid the ads. THERE IS NO PAID VERSION. 30 ads times 30 seconds makes 15 minutes wasted in ads per hour of play. Plus to get an extra ‚Äúundo‚Äù or an additional sorting bottle, you also have to watch an ad. If you swipe between apps or if a call comes through then you again have to watch an ad before you come back to the game. 

If you are fine wasting hours of your time per day watching ads, then give it a try.  Otherwise, I suggest you find a paid game for $3-5 and save yourself time and use it enjoying fun entertainment

Use up the ‚Äúback‚Äù button more than 5 times and there are more ads (Ok with this).  Still, there are so many ads for everything else‚Ä¶ I simply decided to erase the game.  Thanks for the fun but no thanks for the ads‚Ä¶ not enough fun to watch all the junk and (I forgot!) the still ads at the bottom of the page‚Ä¶ one false move and boom! You are at another page.  Stand against these developers and let them know that over advertising is NOT what we download the games for.***at no point in this review I wanted to portray disrespect‚Ä¶ rather emphasis on the disappointment***
